      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SLICK SILAS (2) ran a good time (26.10) when placing three back at this track but has missed the frame since, last time out finishing fourth (26.02) at this track. Meets a moderate line up and rates on top this time. TINY MAC (1) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at Wagga over 400m behind Boracay Beauty (23.99) in a Grade 5. Was in the money the start prior. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to her name from five starts. Better than last start and can bounce back. MANSON LAMPS (5) comes off an average effort last start when eighth at this track over 457m behind Viva La Ziva (26.70) in a Grade 5. Was in the money the start prior. Has never been out of the placings from three starts out of this box. Cannot be taken lightly. JACOBITE KNIFE (6) is a last start winner from this box who must be respected.",
